<div class="col order-1 order-sm-2 details">

<h3 class="h1"><a href="/hinduism/book/rig-veda-english-translation">Rig Veda (translation and commentary)</a></h3>
<p class="props p-0">

by H. H. Wilson | 1866 | 1,999,864 words | ISBN-10: 8171101380 | ISBN-13: 9788171101382 </p>
<div class="tags">
<span class="badge badge-light"><a href="/hinduism">Hinduism</a></span>
</div>

<div class="my-2">
<a href="https://www.exoticindiaart.com/book/details/IDE751/aff11436/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="Buy book now" class="btn btn-info"><i class="fas fa-shopping-cart"></i> Buy now!</a>
</div>

<p class="pb-2">The Rig-Veda, English translation, including the commentary of Sayana and grammatical analysis. The hyms of the Rigveda Samhita represents some of the oldest and complex of Hindu Sanskrit literature. In ten books, these mantras form the core essence of rituals and ceremonies once widely performed throughout ancient India.

This edition contains the...</p>
<p class="disclaimer">Disclaimer: These are translations of Sanskrit texts and are not necessarily approved by everyone associated with the traditions connected to these texts. Consult the source and original scripture in case of doubt.</p>
</div>
</div>	</section>

<section class="col-12 heading">
<div class="inner">
<h1 class="h2 pt-2">Rig Veda 4.1.2</h1>

<div class="row justify-content-between mt-2 pb-2 no-gutters">

<div class="col-auto col-sm-auto order-1">
